        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 7:46PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 742 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Conrad, moving northeast at 25 mph. Additional
thunderstorms extended south roughly along I-15 through eastern
Teton County. In addition to wind gusts in excess of 50 mph, hail up
to one half inch in diameter is possible beneath the stronger cell
approaching Ledger.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shelby, Conrad, Brady, Collins, Ledger, Devon, and Dunkirk.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
